Versioned OTA migration scripts placed in this directory are run by
/usr/sbin/pgenerator-update after the latest cumulative overlay tarball is
extracted.

Rules:
- Name each script with a leading semantic version, for example:
  2.2.3-remove-obsolete-files.sh
  2.2.4-migrate-config-layout.sh
- A script runs when its version is greater than the installed version and
  less than or equal to the target version being installed.
- Keep scripts idempotent. Users may jump across multiple releases in one OTA
  update, so each script must be safe to run exactly once in a cumulative path.
- Use these scripts for one-time data moves, cleanup of obsolete files, or any
  compatibility fix that cannot be handled by shipping the latest full overlay
  alone.

Environment variables passed to each script:
- PG_UPDATE_FROM
- PG_UPDATE_TO
- PG_MIGRATION_VERSION